cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with facial dynamics and image processing techniques to classify posed and spontaneous smiles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep convolutional neural network (CNN) and optical flow also suggests the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of support vector machines (SVM) for classification, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on identifying emotions and state of mind of an individual suggests the possibility of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of normalization procedures and histogram of gradient (HOG) features suggests the possibility of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
